You misuse annotation *@Embeddable*. See description in oracle docs https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/6/api/javax/persistence/Embeddable.html

&gt;Defines a class whose instances are stored as an intrinsic part of an owning entity and share the identity of the entity. Each of the persistent properties or fields of the embedded object is mapped to the database table for the entit

*@Embeddable* annotation makes sense only for singular assotiation fields. Annotating list fields as *@Embeddable* is wrong.

Just replace

    @Embeddable
    public class ExternalLogin {

to

    @Entity
    public class ExternalLogin {

